      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EKARA NAVAJO (9) was out of the money two runs ago then overcame a break to finish second, beaten 2.25 metres, over 2185m at Pinjarra eight days ago. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw. Won't find this any harder and she go one better. OUR MAJOR JACK NZ (2) finished third last time out, beaten 6 metres, in a far better performance at this track over 2130m. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Meets a similar line up so he is capable of taking this out. MYSTA MOON WALKER (8) must be considered after he finished runner-up over 2130m here a week ago. Top-three credentials. BET ON THE RIVER (6) found form and finished in the money two runs ago then came back to earth when he broke and finished fourth last start over 2560m at Northam, coming home 21 metres from the winner. This doesn't look as hard so he is capable of turning things around.",
